@startmindmap namespaces
title Snarf namespace — assembled mount table (spec 02)

* /
** dev
*** draw — draw device (spec 03)
**** new — open to allocate a client conn
**** 1/ — per-client: ctl, data, refresh, colormap
*** mouse — logical mouse events (spec 04)
*** cursor — write to set cursor
*** kbd — keyboard runes (spec 04)
*** cons — console text I/O
*** snarf — clipboard (read/write)
*** storage/ — persistent files (IndexedDB-backed)
*** notify — write "title\\nbody" to notify
*** location — read URL / write to navigate
*** title — read/write tab title
*** log — write → browser console
*** input/ctl — select profile (native/modifier/touch/chordbar)
*** dom/ — the hosting page's DOM
**** root/ — <html> element as a directory
***** ctl — mutate: create/append/remove/listen
***** attrs — one "name value" per line
***** style — computed style, writable subset
***** text — textContent
***** html — innerHTML
***** 0/ 1/ ... — child elements, in order
**** events — stream of subscribed DOM events
**** query — write CSS selector, read matches
** mnt
*** host/ — user-granted local dir (FS Access API)
*** opfs/ — origin-private FS (always available)
*** origin/ — origin server 9P export (if present)
*** snarf-self/ — Snarf's own state, ACME-style
**** index — list of windows
**** new/ — open to create a window
**** 1/ — per-window: addr, body, tag, data, event, ctl
@endmindmap
